**EDIT**

If you want to avoid the deprecated call to `injector.get` but still be able to access the service from the injector with a string, you can use a service to figure out which injection token should be used. I don&#39;t think this is the prettiest way to do it, but I think it meets OPs needs.

First create a Service to map a string to the expected injection token:

